post_survey.medium: Apple Music, Apple car play, YouTube, Radio
post_survey.activities: I do activities such as: cleaning the house, driving, folding clothes, sitting outside, talking a walk, taking a shower, etc while listening to music.
post_survey.habit_change: I've always listened to a variety of music because of my mother. I still listen to Journey and older R&B and soul groups. Growing up in my day we had MTV and Vh1 music to watch while getting ready for school, so that exposed us to more soft rock and pop artist. In middle school, I strictly listened to country music. Now I still listen to a variety of genres such as Alternative artist Lewis Capaldi. My favorite genre is still R&B. It is my most played playlist the I love to sing along to.
post_survey.habits: Overall, I feel as though I have an R&B soul, but I love and have been exposed to most if not all genres throughout my life. I was familiar with 90% of the songs played.
